events.description: Constantius III becomes co-emperor of the Western Roman Empire.
events.html: • 421 – Constantius III becomes co-emperor of the Western Roman Empire.[1]

events.description: The Mongols burn the Russian city of Vladimir.
events.html: • 1238 – The Mongols burn the Russian city of Vladimir.[2][3]

events.description: Seventh Crusade: Crusaders engage Ayyubid forces in the Battle of Al Mansurah.
events.html: • 1250 – Seventh Crusade: Crusaders engage Ayyubid forces in the Battle of Al Mansurah.[4]

events.description: The Byzantine civil war of 1341–47 ends with a power-sharing agreement between John VI Kantakouzenos and John V Palaiologos.
events.html: • 1347 – The Byzantine civil war of 1341–47 ends with a power-sharing agreement between John VI Kantakouzenos and John V Palaiologos.[5][6]

events.description: Mary, Queen of Scots is executed on suspicion of having been involved in the Babington Plot to murder her cousin, Queen Elizabeth I.
events.html: • 1587 – Mary, Queen of Scots is executed on suspicion of having been involved in the Babington Plot to murder her cousin, Queen Elizabeth I.[7][8]

events.description: Robert Devereux, 2nd Earl of Essex, unsuccessfully rebels against Queen Elizabeth I.
events.html: • 1601 – Robert Devereux, 2nd Earl of Essex, unsuccessfully rebels against Queen Elizabeth I.[9][10]

events.description: The College of William & Mary in Williamsburg, Virginia, the second-oldest institution of higher education in the Thirteen Colonies, is granted a charter by King William III and Queen Mary II.
events.html: • 1693 – The College of William & Mary in Williamsburg, Virginia, the second-oldest institution of higher education in the Thirteen Colonies, is granted a charter by King William III and Queen Mary II.[11]

events.description: Napoleon defeats the coalition forces of Russian General Bennigsen and Prussian General L'Estocq at the Battle of Eylau.
events.html: • 1807 – Napoleon defeats the coalition forces of Russian General Bennigsen and Prussian General L'Estocq at the Battle of Eylau.[12][13]

events.description: An army led by Grand Marshal Las Heras crosses the Andes to join San Martín in the liberation of Chile from Spain.
events.html: • 1817 – An army led by Grand Marshal Las Heras crosses the Andes to join San Martín in the liberation of Chile from Spain.[14][15]

events.description: Richard Johnson becomes the first and only Vice President of the United States chosen by the Senate.
events.html: • 1837 – Richard Johnson becomes the first and only Vice President of the United States chosen by the Senate.[16][17]

entities.name: Vice President of the United States

events.description: Delaware refuses to ratify the Thirteenth Amendment to the U.S. Constitution, delaying the criminalization of slavery until the amendment's national adoption on December 6, 1865. The amendment is ultimately ratified by Delaware on February 12, 1901, the 92nd anniversary of Abraham Lincoln's birth.
events.html: • 1865 – Delaware refuses to ratify the Thirteenth Amendment to the U.S. Constitution, delaying the criminalization of slavery until the amendment's national adoption on December 6, 1865.[18][19] The amendment is ultimately ratified by Delaware on February 12, 1901, the 92nd anniversary of Abraham Lincoln's birth.[20][21]

entities.name: Thirteenth Amendment to the U.S. Constitution

events.description: Sandford Fleming first proposes the adoption of Universal Standard Time at a meeting of the Royal Canadian Institute.
events.html: • 1879 – Sandford Fleming first proposes the adoption of Universal Standard Time at a meeting of the Royal Canadian Institute.[22][23]

events.description: England's cricket team, led by Lord Harris, is attacked in a riot during a match in Sydney.
events.html: • 1879 – England's cricket team, led by Lord Harris, is attacked in a riot during a match in Sydney.[24]

events.description: The first Japanese immigrants arrive in Hawaii.
events.html: • 1885 – The first Japanese immigrants arrive in Hawaii.[25][26]

events.description: The Dawes Act is enacted, authorizing the U.S. President to divide Native American tribal land into individual allotments.
events.html: • 1887 – The Dawes Act is enacted, authorizing the U.S. President to divide Native American tribal land into individual allotments.[27][28][29]

entities.name: Native Americans in the United States
List of Indian reservations in the United States

events.description: Japanese forces launch a surprise attack against Russian-controlled Port Arthur, marking the start of the Russo-Japanese war.
events.html: • 1904 – Japanese forces launch a surprise attack against Russian-controlled Port Arthur, marking the start of the Russo-Japanese war.[30][31]

events.description: The Dutch Colonial Army's Marechaussee regiment led by General G.C.E. van Daalen launch a military campaign in the Dutch East Indies' Northern Sumatra region, leading to the deaths of thousands of civilians.
events.html: • 1904 – The Dutch Colonial Army's Marechaussee regiment led by General G.C.E. van Daalen launch a military campaign in the Dutch East Indies' Northern Sumatra region, leading to the deaths of thousands of civilians.[32][33][34]

events.description: The Boy Scouts of America is incorporated by William D. Boyce.
events.html: • 1910 – The Boy Scouts of America is incorporated by William D. Boyce.[35][36]

events.description: D. W. Griffith's controversial landmark film The Birth of a Nation premieres in Los Angeles.
events.html: • 1915 – D. W. Griffith's controversial landmark film The Birth of a Nation premieres in Los Angeles.[37]

events.description: The first state execution in the United States by gas chamber takes place in Nevada.
events.html: • 1924 – The first state execution in the United States by gas chamber takes place in Nevada.[38][39]

entities.name: Capital punishment in the United States

events.description: Spanish Civil War: Republican forces establish the Interprovincial Council of Santander, Palencia and Burgos in Cantabria.
events.html: • 1937 – Spanish Civil War: Republican forces establish the Interprovincial Council of Santander, Palencia and Burgos in Cantabria.[40]

entities.name: Interprovincial Council of Santander, Palencia and Burgos

events.description: World War II: Japan invades Singapore.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: Japan invades Singapore.[41][42]

events.description: World War II: British and Canadian forces commence Operation Veritable to occupy land between the Maas and Rhine rivers.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: British and Canadian forces commence Operation Veritable to occupy land between the Maas and Rhine rivers.[43]

events.description: World War II: Mikhail Devyataev escapes with nine other Soviet POWs from a Nazi concentration camp in Peenemünde, Usedom.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Mikhail Devyataev escapes with nine other Soviet POWs from a Nazi concentration camp in Peenemünde, Usedom.[44]

events.description: The People's Republic of Korea is dissolved in the North and replaced by the communist-controlled Provisional People's Committee of North Korea.
events.html: • 1946 – The People's Republic of Korea is dissolved in the North and replaced by the communist-controlled Provisional People's Committee of North Korea.[45]

entities.name: Provisional People's Committee of North Korea

events.description: The Stasi, the secret police of East Germany, is established.
events.html: • 1950 – The Stasi, the secret police of East Germany, is established.[46][47]

events.description: Queen Elizabeth II issues an Order-in-Council, proclaiming the House of Windsor and declaring that her descendants will take the name Mountbatten-Windsor.
events.html: • 1960 – Queen Elizabeth II issues an Order-in-Council, proclaiming the House of Windsor and declaring that her descendants will take the name Mountbatten-Windsor.[48][49]

events.description: The Hollywood Walk of Fame is founded.
events.html: • 1960 – The Hollywood Walk of Fame is founded.[50]

events.description: Nine protestors are killed at Charonne station, Paris, by French police under the command of ex-Vichy official and Parisian Prefect of Police Maurice Papon.
events.html: • 1962 – Nine protestors are killed at Charonne station, Paris, by French police under the command of ex-Vichy official and Parisian Prefect of Police Maurice Papon.[51][52]

events.description: The regime of Prime Minister of Iraq Abd al-Karim Qasim is overthrown by the Ba'ath Party.
events.html: • 1963 – The regime of Prime Minister of Iraq Abd al-Karim Qasim is overthrown by the Ba'ath Party.[53][54][55]

events.description: Eastern Air Lines Flight 663 crashes into the Atlantic Ocean and explodes, killing all 84 people onboard.
events.html: • 1965 – Eastern Air Lines Flight 663 crashes into the Atlantic Ocean and explodes, killing all 84 people onboard.[56][57]

events.description: American civil rights movement: An attack on Black students from South Carolina State University who are protesting racial segregation leaves three dead and 28 injured in Orangeburg, South Carolina.
events.html: • 1968 – American civil rights movement: An attack on Black students from South Carolina State University who are protesting racial segregation leaves three dead and 28 injured in Orangeburg, South Carolina.[58][59]

events.description: The NASDAQ stock market index opens for the first time.
events.html: • 1971 – The NASDAQ stock market index opens for the first time.[60][61]

events.description: South Vietnamese ground troops launch an incursion into Laos to try to cut off the Ho Chi Minh trail and stop communist infiltration into the country.
events.html: • 1971 – South Vietnamese ground troops launch an incursion into Laos to try to cut off the Ho Chi Minh trail and stop communist infiltration into the country.[62][63]

entities.name: Army of the Republic of Vietnam

events.description: The crew of Skylab 4, the last mission to visit the American space station Skylab, returns to Earth after 84 days in space.
events.html: • 1974 – The crew of Skylab 4, the last mission to visit the American space station Skylab, returns to Earth after 84 days in space.[64][65][66]

events.description: A dust storm hits Melbourne, resulting in the worst drought on record and severe weather conditions in the city.
events.html: • 1983 – A dust storm hits Melbourne, resulting in the worst drought on record and severe weather conditions in the city.[67]

events.description: Irish race horse Shergar is stolen and allegedly killed by gunmen in a ransom attempt by the PIRA.
events.html: • 1983 – Irish race horse Shergar is stolen and allegedly killed by gunmen in a ransom attempt by the PIRA.[68]

events.description: Twenty-three people are killed when a VIA Rail passenger train collides with a Canadian National freight train near the town of Hinton, Alberta, making it one of the worst rail accidents in Canada.
events.html: • 1986 – Twenty-three people are killed when a VIA Rail passenger train collides with a Canadian National freight train near the town of Hinton, Alberta, making it one of the worst rail accidents in Canada.[69][70]

events.description: Independent Air Flight 1851 strikes Pico Alto mountain while on approach to Santa Maria Airport in the Azores, killing all 144 passengers on board.
events.html: • 1989 – Independent Air Flight 1851 strikes Pico Alto mountain while on approach to Santa Maria Airport in the Azores, killing all 144 passengers on board.[71][72]

events.description: An Iran Air Tours Tupolev Tu-154 and an Iranian Air Force Sukhoi Su-24 collide mid-air near Qods, Iran, killing all 133 people onboard both aircraft.
events.html: • 1993 – An Iran Air Tours Tupolev Tu-154 and an Iranian Air Force Sukhoi Su-24 collide mid-air near Qods, Iran, killing all 133 people onboard both aircraft.[73][74]

entities.name: Islamic Republic of Iran Air Force

events.description: Over 2 miles (3.2 km) of road are buried after a storm in the Hindu Kush mountains of Afghanistan triggers a series of avalanches, killing at least 172 people and trapping over 2,000 others.
events.html: • 2010 – Over 2 miles (3.2 km) of road are buried after a storm in the Hindu Kush mountains of Afghanistan triggers a series of avalanches, killing at least 172 people and trapping over 2,000 others.[75][76]
